{{other people|David Grove|David Grove (disambiguation)}}
'''David C. Grove''' (born 1935)<ref>{{cite LAF|id=n81-85703}}</ref> is an American [[anthropologist]], [[archaeologist]] and academic, known for his contributions and research into the [[Mesoamerican chronology|Preclassic (or Formative) period]] cultures of [[Mesoamerica]], in particular those of the [[Mexican altiplano|Mexican ''altiplano'']] and [[Gulf Coast of Mexico|Gulf Coast]] regions. A lecturer and professor at [[University of Illinois at Urbana-Champaign]] (UIUC) for some thirty years, Grove retains a position as Professor [[Emeritus]] of Anthropology at UIUC and is also designated a Courtesy Professor of Anthropology at the [[University of Florida]].

