'''Matthew J. Adams''' is an [[Archaeology|archaeologist]] who specializes in the [[Near East]]. He earned his degrees at [[Pennsylvania State University]] and the [[University of California, Los Angeles]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.archaeological.org/lecturer/matthewjadams|title=Matthew J. Adams - Archaeological Institute of America|website=www.archaeological.org|language=en|access-date=2018-05-12}}</ref> and is the director of the [[Albright Institute of Archaeological Research]] in Jerusalem and the president of American Archaeology Abroad, Inc.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://aiar.academia.edu/MatthewJAdams|title=Matthew J Adams {{!}} W.F. Albright Institute of Archaeological Research - Academia.edu|website=aiar.academia.edu|language=en|access-date=2018-05-12}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.aiar.org/albright-news-no-17-2012/|title=Matthew J. Adams, Incoming Director of the W. F. Albright Institute {{!}} AIAR|website=www.aiar.org|access-date=2018-05-12}}</ref> He has worked on several archaeological projects in the past, and is currently director of the Jezreel Valley Regional Project<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.jezreelvalleyregionalproject.com/people-and-groups.html|title=People and Groups|website=www.jezreelvalleyregionalproject.com|language=en-US|access-date=2018-05-12}}</ref> and Co-Director of the Megiddo Expedition along with [[Israel Finkelstein]] and Mario Martin.<ref>{{cite web |title=The Staff |url=https://megiddoexpedition.wordpress.com/the-staff/ |website=The Megiddo Expedition |accessdate=25 October 2018}}</ref>

